channel.title: How to make a package exist? REP++
channel.description: So randomly, my compiler brings up a bunch of errors saying that the package sign does not exist, import sign.signlink... but in all of the files that the compiler shows... sign.sign link is already imported there... so does anyone have any ideas how to make my sign exist? lol Please someone help, I'm hosting a server and i need to make a webclient, but i cant with my compiler geeked up.

item.title: How to make a package exist? REP++
item.dc:creator: @Mendorphins Mendorphins
item.description:
@Mendorphins wrote:

Are you sure it’s not Signlink? Case sensitive. Copy and paste the import.

It should be import sign.Signlink; (if it’s capitalised).
